Infrastructure description

This infrastructure is a simple web stack hosting the website www.foobar.com
. A user accesses the website through a browser by entering the domain name.

The domain name foobar.com is configured with a www DNS A record that points to the server IP address 8.8.8.8. The DNS system translates the domain name into the server’s IP address so the browser can locate it.

The server (8.8.8.8) hosts all components of the web infrastructure, including a web server (Nginx), an application server, application codebase, and a MySQL database.

The web server (Nginx) receives HTTP requests from users and serves static content or forwards dynamic requests to the application server.

The application server executes the business logic of the application and communicates with the database when data is required.

The database (MySQL) stores and manages application data such as user information and content.

Communication between the user`s computer and the server happens using HTTP/HTTPS over TCP/IP.

Issues with this infrastructure
Single Point of Failure (SPOF): if the server goes down, the entire website becomes unavailable.
Maintenance downtime: restarting or updating any component causes the website to be unavailable.
Lack of scalability: a single server cannot handle high traffic efficiently.
